Unsolved Practical: Create an HTML document that includes a navigation bar with several links. Use CSS Flexbox to style these links as follows:
•	Align the links horizontally within the navigation bar.
•	Apply equal spacing between the links.
•	Center the links vertically within the navigation bar.
•	Add padding and a background color to each link when hovered over.


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Navigation Bar</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <nav class="nav-bar">
        <ul class="nav-links">
            <li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">About</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">Services</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">Contact</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>
</body>
</html>

.nav-bar {
    background-color: #333;
    padding: 10px;
}

.nav-links {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
}

.nav-links li {
    margin-right: 20px;
}

.nav-links a {
    color: #fff;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background-color 0.3s ease;
}

.nav-links a:hover {
    background-color: #444;
    padding: 10px;
    border-radius: 5px;
}



